The Kano State Public Complaints and Anti-Corruption Commission (PCACC) says it has developed new skills and strategies in its fight against corruption. The Commission’s chairman, Mr Muhiyi Magaji  disclosed this in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) shortly after the meeting on documentation of the anti-graft strategy in Dutse on Monday. Magaji, who declined to go into specific details of the skills and strategies, stated that the meeting was sponsored by the European Union (EU). He said that the Kano anti-graft agency was determined in the war against corruption in all its ramification as well as in ensuring a free and egalitarian society. NAN reports that relevant stakeholders in the fight against corruption, including the ministry of justice, civil society organisations  (CSOs) as well as and representatives of the media attended the meeting.